rComments: The course is kind of bird compare to other hardcore mathematical finance course, but as the course name suggest (apm: applied math), the course focused more on application. Professor Seco made everything clear, and gives us super useful assignment that engaged with real world data(what you will be doing in real financial jobs).
You don't need to attend lecture to get an A. What you only need is past exams and tests.

He will spend half of the lecture on proofs that you won't be tested on. Found that going to the class confused me more than helped. Stopped going to that class a long time ago but doing well in the course because math TAs are helpful and tests are basic so far.
Very good professor.  Knowledgeable and has extremely impressive credentials.

Seco sucks..I've never had a worse math teacher in my life..he makes you feel stupid if you dont know something..a famous line of his is "who has never seen this before, you should have seen this in grade 5"...ummm no i didnt.  His tests aren't that bad, but you need to teach yourself.  SECO SUCKS!!!
He's a kewl proff. Knows what he's talkin about.
